name: Labor Day
summary: The United States celebrates Labor Day on the first Monday of September to commemorate the contributions of workers to the nation's prosperity. This year, the holiday falls on September 4th. Labor Day has its roots in the late 19th century when the labor movement fought for better working conditions and recognition of workers' rights. Maine and Binghamton University are hosting Labor Day events, while CNN Underscored is highlighting the best Labor Day sales. The Department of Transportation predicts a surge in airline passengers this holiday weekend, surpassing pre-pandemic levels. The City of Upper Arlington will host the 2024 Labor Day Arts Festival, and Boston University encourages residents to celebrate with local events. The Air Force has announced special operating hours for its bases during the holiday, and NPR reports on the expected increase in airline passenger traffic. Finally, USA TODAY provides historical context and explains the significance of Labor Day.

name: Frances Tiafoe
summary: In a highly anticipated rematch at the US Open, Frances Tiafoe emerged victorious over fellow American Ben Shelton in a thrilling five-set marathon. Tiafoe will now face Alexei Popyrin in the third round. Shelton and Tiafoe will meet again in the 2024 US Open. Tiafoe's victory was hard-fought, as he outdueled Shelton in an all-American epic that captivated the fans. The match showcased the rising stars of American tennis and marked the first time that two Americans faced each other in the second round of the US Open since 2004. Prior to the game, Tiafoe had prepared by listening to the music of Nipsey Hussle.

name: Brian Kelly
summary: After LSU's disappointing loss to USC, Head Coach Brian Kelly has expressed frustration and anger. Kelly believes his team lacked discipline and killer instinct, leading to the upset defeat. Despite this setback, Kelly is still making progress in weaning LSU off the transfer portal. Kelly has also spoken out against Oklahoma State's use of QR code helmets, emphasizing the importance of tradition in the game. While some have been critical of Kelly's performance in his third year, ESPN acknowledges that both he and USC's Lincoln Riley are facing critical seasons. Despite the challenges, Kelly remains confident in LSU's ability to succeed, going so far as to boldly declare that the team is "in a great position to go beat the pants off of USC."

name: Tetairoa McMillan
summary: In the season opener, Arizona wide receiver Tetairoa McMillan shattered the university's single-game receiving record with an astounding 304 yards and four touchdowns. His dominant performance played a pivotal role in Arizona's 61-39 victory over New Mexico, marking a victorious debut for new head coach Brent Brennan. McMillan's exceptional outing garnered widespread attention, with experts projecting him as one of ESPN's top 25 NFL draft prospects for 2025. The emergence of McMillan, along with other talented players like quarterback Noah Fifita, has instilled confidence within the Arizona program, as they aim to challenge for success in the competitive Pac-12 conference.
